SIMPLE: glutton
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glutton
<hw>Glut"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>glotoun</ets>, <ets>glotun</ets>, F. <ets>glouton</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>gluto</ets>, <ets>glutto</ets>. See <er>Glut</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who eats voraciously, or to excess; a
gormandizer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: One who gluts himself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Gluttons</qex> in murder, wanton to destroy.</q>
<rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A carnivorous mammal (<spn>Gulo
gulo</spn> formerly <spn>Gulo luscus</spn>), of the weasel family
<fam>Mustelid⟦ae⟧</fam>, about the size of a large badger; called also
<altname>wolverine</altname>, <altname>wolverene</altname> and
<altname>carcajou</altname>. It was formerly believed to be inordinately
voracious, whence the name. It is a native of the northern parts of
America, Europe, and Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Glutton bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the giant
fulmar (<spn>Ossifraga gigantea</spn>); -- called also <altname>Mother
Carey's goose</altname>, and <altname>mollymawk</altname>.</cd></cs> <--
glutton for punishment = one persistent in an effort in spite of harmful
results -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glutton</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glutton
<hw>Glut"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Gluttonous; greedy;
gormandizing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Glutton</xex> souls.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>glutton</qex> monastery in former ages makes a hungry
ministry in our days.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glutton</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Glutton
<hw>Glut"ton</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To glut; to eat
voraciously.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Gluttoned</qex> at last, return at home to pine.</q>
<rj><qau>Lovelace.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whereon in Egypt <qex>gluttoning</qex> they fed.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gluttonish</ent>⟦br⟧
